Explanation:

The problem requires finding the minimum number of operations needed to make either num1 or num2 equal to 0. We can solve this problem using two nested while loops. The outer loop subtracts num2 from num1 until num1 becomes 0, and the inner loop subtracts num1 from num2 until num2 becomes 0. The result variable keeps track of the number of operations performed.

The time complexity is O(min(num1, num2)) because the loops will terminate as soon as either num1 or num2 becomes 0. The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a single variable (result) and do not allocate any additional memory. The energy implications are low because the algorithm does not involve any intensive operations or resource usage.

